WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.881 --> 00:00:07.674
You need to think
outside the box.

2
00:00:07.757 --> 00:00:09.384
You told me you killed 33 boys.

3
00:00:09.467 --> 00:00:10.928
It shouldn't be your first case.

4
00:00:11.011 --> 00:00:12.095
Not my first case?

5
00:00:12.178 --> 00:00:13.263
You're not gonna
get a fair trial here.

6
00:00:13.346 --> 00:00:14.681
We could motion
to hold the jury selection

7
00:00:14.764 --> 00:00:15.682
somewhere else.

8
00:00:15.765 --> 00:00:17.059
I'm looking for Jeffrey Rignall.

9
00:00:17.142 --> 00:00:18.310
-What do you want?
-Last year.

10
00:00:18.393 --> 00:00:20.187
you filed a police report
for assault.

11
00:00:20.270 --> 00:00:21.355
You named Gacy as the assailant.

12
00:00:21.438 --> 00:00:22.981
In light of your psych evals.

13
00:00:23.064 --> 00:00:24.733
we're advising you
plead not guilty

14
00:00:24.816 --> 00:00:25.776
by reason of insanity.

15
00:00:25.859 --> 00:00:27.069
How about we plead innocent

16
00:00:27.152 --> 00:00:28.320
by reason of self-defense?

17
00:00:28.403 --> 00:00:29.696
He said if I gave him
what he wanted.

18
00:00:29.779 --> 00:00:30.781
he would give me more money.

19
00:00:30.864 --> 00:00:32.991
So you're not a victim?
You're a whore.

20
00:00:33.074 --> 00:00:34.451
Bessie: Love you.

21
00:00:36.077 --> 00:00:37.871
And it's welded.
Ain't going nowhere.

22
00:00:37.954 --> 00:00:39.247
Where were you
at ID-ing the victims?

23
00:00:39.330 --> 00:00:40.624
Billy: There's a good guy
out there for you.

24
00:00:40.707 --> 00:00:42.334
He's a guy that
you can be really proud of.

25
00:00:42.417 --> 00:00:44.419
So shut the hell up and be him.

26
00:00:44.502 --> 00:00:45.796
Get a real job.

27
00:00:45.879 --> 00:00:47.464
-Never turn a trick alone.
-Why?

28
00:00:47.547 --> 00:00:50.133
Ivy: 'Cause that's how
you go missing. forever.

29
00:00:50.216 --> 00:00:51.885
[singing] Happy birthday.

30
00:00:51.968 --> 00:00:54.554
All right.
I'll be in the car. Go.

31
00:00:54.637 --> 00:00:56.431
Yes! Thank you.

32
00:00:56.514 --> 00:00:57.557
[laughs]

33
00:00:57.640 --> 00:00:59.518
You really scared me there.
Mr. Gacy.

34
00:00:59.601 --> 00:01:01.770
Just one more trick
for the road.

35
00:01:08.568 --> 00:01:10.654
Reporter: [indistinct] the
discovery of Rob Piest's body?

36
00:01:10.737 --> 00:01:12.948
Sam: We're thankful
that Rob Piest's body

37
00:01:13.031 --> 00:01:14.199
has been recovered...

38
00:01:14.282 --> 00:01:17.953
but my client is still
entitled to due process

39
00:01:18.036 --> 00:01:19.329
afforded by the Constitution.

40
00:01:19.412 --> 00:01:21.373
We're not reverting to. uh.
mob rule and lynchings

41
00:01:21.456 --> 00:01:23.584
as much as the prosecution
has pushed for that.

42
00:01:23.667 --> 00:01:25.043
[chattering indistinctly]

43
00:01:25.126 --> 00:01:27.045
Bill: Listen.
this is all I'm gonna say.

44
00:01:27.128 --> 00:01:30.257
In light of the newly
discovered bodies.

45
00:01:30.340 --> 00:01:32.092
we will be amending the charges.

46
00:01:32.175 --> 00:01:35.762
uh. bringing it to
a total of 33 murders.

47
00:01:35.845 --> 00:01:36.847
[elevator bell rings] Excuse me.

48
00:01:36.930 --> 00:01:40.142
[reporters overlapping
chattering]

49
00:01:40.225 --> 00:01:41.602
Gacy was. uh.

50
00:01:41.685 --> 00:01:44.271
suffering from chest pains
and had a heart attack.

51
00:01:44.354 --> 00:01:45.397
Reporter:
And these are real symptoms?

52
00:01:45.480 --> 00:01:47.399
I assure you.
he... he's not faking it.

53
00:01:47.482 --> 00:01:49.401
He has a long history
of cardiac issues.

54
00:01:49.484 --> 00:01:50.444
He's been in and out
of the hospital.

55
00:01:50.527 --> 00:01:52.988
requires real medical attention.

56
00:01:53.071 --> 00:01:55.282
The insanity defense
is nothing short

57
00:01:55.365 --> 00:01:57.200
of a Sam Amirante Hail Mary.

58
00:01:57.283 --> 00:01:58.994
I have nothing more to say
on the matter.

59
00:01:59.077 --> 00:02:00.245
It is stupid.
-It's true.

60
00:02:00.328 --> 00:02:03.081
Gacy had been fasting
for 20 days.

61
00:02:03.164 --> 00:02:05.042
consuming nothing but liquids.

62
00:02:05.125 --> 00:02:07.377
Uh. it was not
a hunger strike per se.

63
00:02:07.460 --> 00:02:10.255
But. uh.
Gacy is a very religious man.

64
00:02:10.338 --> 00:02:12.299
And. uh.
Easter's around the corner.

65
00:02:12.382 --> 00:02:14.593
So. you know
who else fasted. Jesus.

66
00:02:14.676 --> 00:02:17.721
We are very pleased that
Judge Garippo has denied

67
00:02:17.804 --> 00:02:20.432
the defense's request
for a change of venue.

68
00:02:20.515 --> 00:02:23.518
However. agreeing to impanel
a jury from a different county

69
00:02:23.601 --> 00:02:26.229
is going to delay the trial
another three weeks.

70
00:02:26.312 --> 00:02:27.981
Um. if you ask me.

71
00:02:28.064 --> 00:02:30.108
this is Mr. Amirante's plan
all along.

72
00:02:30.191 --> 00:02:33.111
A potential juror
yelled out in court.

73
00:02:33.194 --> 00:02:34.571
saying my client is guilty.

74
00:02:34.654 --> 00:02:36.490
I had no choice
but to file for a mistrial.

75
00:02:36.573 --> 00:02:39.117
Now the judge
rejected the motion.

76
00:02:39.200 --> 00:02:42.329
but the law is clear.
the jury pool is poisoned.

77
00:02:42.412 --> 00:02:44.122
And these are Rockford jurists.

78
00:02:44.205 --> 00:02:45.791
Imagine if they had been
impaneled in Chicago.

79
00:02:45.874 --> 00:02:47.292
-Are you suggesting that...
-I mean. look.

80
00:02:47.375 --> 00:02:49.419
Maybe Bill Kunkle can
finally stop whining about

81
00:02:49.502 --> 00:02:52.422
being cooped up in Rockford
for the selection process.

82
00:02:52.505 --> 00:02:53.799
I highly doubt it
knowing that man. but...

83
00:02:53.882 --> 00:02:56.343
Bill: I can understand
why the Clowning Association

84
00:02:56.426 --> 00:02:59.680
would hold a press conference
to defend their profession.

85
00:02:59.763 --> 00:03:03.225
But no. we will not be calling
any clowns to the witness stand.

86
00:03:03.308 --> 00:03:04.935
It's been a long 14 months.

87
00:03:05.018 --> 00:03:08.397
but I'm prepared to wage
a street-fighter style battle

88
00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:11.483
in court for John Wayne Gacy's

89
00:03:11.566 --> 00:03:14.152
God-given rights
as an American citizen.

90
00:03:14.235 --> 00:03:17.072
Bob Motta and I are tough.
aggressive lawyers.

91
00:03:17.155 --> 00:03:18.740
gladiators in a three-piece.

92
00:03:18.823 --> 00:03:20.450
We do not hold back.

93
00:03:20.533 --> 00:03:22.869
Thank you. everybody.
and I'll see you in court.

94
00:03:22.952 --> 00:03:24.329
[camera shutter clicks]

95
00:03:26.915 --> 00:03:29.918
[indistinct chattering]

96
00:03:32.837 --> 00:03:34.214
Bill: Oh. come on.

97
00:03:34.297 --> 00:03:37.717
Jesus Christ. [sighs]

98
00:03:41.638 --> 00:03:46.393
Sam: [indistinct]
Well. this is awkward.

99
00:03:47.143 --> 00:03:49.312
Only when you say it is.

100
00:03:50.480 --> 00:03:51.564
Bob.

101
00:03:52.065 --> 00:03:54.776
Moo. [chuckles]

102
00:03:55.944 --> 00:03:57.529
Just too hungry to send it back.

103
00:03:57.612 --> 00:03:59.739
Uh. ready for next week?

104
00:03:59.948 --> 00:04:01.741
We ever really ready. Bob?

105
00:04:02.450 --> 00:04:04.703
Just gotta feet first it.

106
00:04:04.786 --> 00:04:06.287
Goddamn right.

107
00:04:07.414 --> 00:04:08.373
I'm gonna grab our table.

108
00:04:08.456 --> 00:04:10.250
Can I order you something?

109
00:04:10.333 --> 00:04:12.628
Yeah. Whatever. uh.
you think I'll like.

110
00:04:12.711 --> 00:04:14.588
Thank you.
-"Whatever you think I'll like?"

111
00:04:14.671 --> 00:04:16.048
Jesus Christ.

112
00:04:16.131 --> 00:04:18.299
You guys make a cute couple.

113
00:04:19.384 --> 00:04:21.469
[clears throat]

114
00:04:23.388 --> 00:04:26.975
Been thinking about last year.

115
00:04:27.475 --> 00:04:31.438
That day. that first day
in court. me and you?

116
00:04:31.521 --> 00:04:34.107
What you told me? To walk away.

117
00:04:34.190 --> 00:04:35.650
Hmm.

118
00:04:37.819 --> 00:04:38.987
Regrets?

119
00:04:39.404 --> 00:04:40.864
I don't know.

120
00:04:41.573 --> 00:04:45.827
I just really thought
I could... handle it.

121
00:04:46.411 --> 00:04:49.622
And. uh. fuck.

122
00:04:50.999 --> 00:04:53.585
[sighs] I mean.

123
00:04:53.668 --> 00:04:55.253
who could've predicted
this circus?

124
00:04:55.545 --> 00:04:57.547
You mean other than everybody?

125
00:04:59.466 --> 00:05:00.717
I'll predict another thing

126
00:05:00.800 --> 00:05:03.804
where my big ass is gonna
end up after I win.

127
00:05:03.887 --> 00:05:05.597
Up on that big-ass bench.

128
00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:07.599
Fifth time's the charm. huh?

129
00:05:07.682 --> 00:05:08.683
Uh-hmm.

130
00:05:09.517 --> 00:05:11.770
Right after
that sick fuck of yours

131
00:05:11.853 --> 00:05:14.064
takes his place in hell.

132
00:05:14.147 --> 00:05:16.108
Is that why you're doing this?

133
00:05:16.191 --> 00:05:17.401
To become a judge?

134
00:05:17.484 --> 00:05:20.362
I'm doing this
because he deserves it.

135
00:05:21.029 --> 00:05:25.575
Everything else is just gravy.
I like gravy.

136
00:05:28.244 --> 00:05:29.913
[sighs]

137
00:05:29.996 --> 00:05:31.540
I just wanted my own practice.

138
00:05:31.623 --> 00:05:34.668
You know hell attracting
new clients is gonna be tough

139
00:05:34.751 --> 00:05:37.379
now that you got
that scarlet letter on you.

140
00:05:37.462 --> 00:05:40.841
When I joined the Marines.
I got picked on.

141
00:05:40.924 --> 00:05:42.134
Uh-hmm.

142
00:05:42.217 --> 00:05:44.719
My size made me an easy target.

143
00:05:45.053 --> 00:05:49.849
Italian Meatball they would
call me. among other things.

144
00:05:50.600 --> 00:05:53.812
Got my ass kicked daily.
yelled at.

145
00:05:53.895 --> 00:05:56.315
just trying to fucking break me.
you know.

146
00:05:56.398 --> 00:05:58.859
But I didn't quit.
-Hmm.

147
00:05:58.942 --> 00:06:00.485
Became the 17th Marine

148
00:06:00.568 --> 00:06:03.822
ever to score a perfect 500
on my physical.

149
00:06:04.364 --> 00:06:06.241
It's in my DNA.

150
00:06:06.533 --> 00:06:08.868
stick with it
till the bitter end.

151
00:06:10.704 --> 00:06:12.831
That's a great story. Sam.

152
00:06:13.665 --> 00:06:17.836
but it's a piss-poor excuse
to let a psychopath walk.

153
00:06:19.004 --> 00:06:23.508
You know. you need
all 12 for a conviction.

154
00:06:23.591 --> 00:06:26.469
I only need one for a hung jury.

155
00:06:28.013 --> 00:06:29.514
Well...

156
00:06:31.266 --> 00:06:32.642
ding. ding.

157
00:06:40.608 --> 00:06:43.362
It's... insanity
doesn't sound pre-meditated.

158
00:06:43.445 --> 00:06:45.030
What part of
what I just told you

159
00:06:45.113 --> 00:06:46.365
doesn't sound pre-meditated?

160
00:06:46.448 --> 00:06:48.158
That's not the issue. Jeff.

161
00:06:48.241 --> 00:06:49.493
You published a book.

162
00:06:49.576 --> 00:06:52.245
in which you state
that Gacy was insane.

163
00:06:52.328 --> 00:06:53.747
out of his mind.
-He is.

164
00:06:53.830 --> 00:06:58.001
We told you to wait until
after the trial to release it.

165
00:06:58.084 --> 00:06:59.211
I knew it. I knew...

166
00:06:59.294 --> 00:07:01.213
When that cop
came to my door last year.

167
00:07:01.296 --> 00:07:02.422
I knew it shouldn't have helped.

168
00:07:02.505 --> 00:07:04.049
You came to me.

169
00:07:04.132 --> 00:07:05.300
Just wait?

170
00:07:05.383 --> 00:07:06.718
I mean. it's.
it's all you people.

171
00:07:06.801 --> 00:07:08.345
you cops. all you ever say.

172
00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:09.888
I'm so tired of waiting.

173
00:07:09.971 --> 00:07:11.181
I wanted my story out.

174
00:07:11.264 --> 00:07:13.809
We have to paint
a clear picture. All right.

175
00:07:13.892 --> 00:07:15.644
The core principle
of our argument

176
00:07:15.727 --> 00:07:17.437
is that Gacy wasn't insane.

177
00:07:17.520 --> 00:07:19.439
that he was clear minded.
pre-meditated.

178
00:07:19.522 --> 00:07:20.482
Yeah. he's all of those things.

179
00:07:20.565 --> 00:07:24.110
It confuses the jury. Jeff.

180
00:07:24.986 --> 00:07:26.905
If you get on the stand
and testify.

181
00:07:26.988 --> 00:07:29.408
the defense is going to
impeach your testimony

182
00:07:29.491 --> 00:07:31.660
with the help of your
own damn book.

183
00:07:31.743 --> 00:07:33.328
You made their argument
for them.

184
00:07:33.411 --> 00:07:34.663
Bill: You know
what else juries hate?

185
00:07:34.746 --> 00:07:37.749
The idea of a witness
profiting from a case.

186
00:07:37.832 --> 00:07:40.419
And as our key witness.
no. none of this is any good.

187
00:07:40.502 --> 00:07:41.502
We can't use you.

188
00:07:41.836 --> 00:07:43.922
It's a sad thing
what happened to you.

189
00:07:44.172 --> 00:07:45.591
A shit situation.

190
00:07:45.674 --> 00:07:48.551
But we only get one shot at this
and we gotta get it right.

191
00:07:49.719 --> 00:07:52.180
-It's my story.
-Uh-huh.

192
00:07:53.890 --> 00:07:56.685
I did what I thought was right.

193
00:07:59.270 --> 00:08:01.231
I'm the victim here.

194
00:08:19.541 --> 00:08:21.168
You have to work
on your bedside manner.

195
00:08:21.251 --> 00:08:22.585
Life's too short.

196
00:08:23.128 --> 00:08:26.256
We need another compelling
witness who knows Gacy.

197
00:08:26.339 --> 00:08:28.175
counter the narrative.
-I understand.

198
00:08:28.258 --> 00:08:30.761
Otherwise. Sam will be doing
his best Brunnhilde.

199
00:08:30.844 --> 00:08:33.638
singing the same insanity note
over and over.

200
00:08:34.264 --> 00:08:36.599
[sighs] All right here.

201
00:08:37.142 --> 00:08:38.310
Divide and conquer.

202
00:08:38.393 --> 00:08:39.645
You take the victims.
I'll take the families.

203
00:08:39.728 --> 00:08:43.023
Spread them out.
I need to see the whole mosaic.

204
00:08:44.733 --> 00:08:48.945
[dramatic music playing]

205
00:09:03.710 --> 00:09:04.878
All right. Obviously.

206
00:09:04.961 --> 00:09:07.005
we're gonna have
the families testify.

207
00:09:07.088 --> 00:09:09.508
All right. They will
emotionally activate the jury.

208
00:09:09.591 --> 00:09:11.051
Save the experts for counter.

209
00:09:11.134 --> 00:09:12.261
I don't know about that.

210
00:09:12.344 --> 00:09:13.553
No. no. I need them to blunt

211
00:09:13.636 --> 00:09:16.139
whatever Sam's
crackpot expert has to say.

212
00:09:16.514 --> 00:09:20.727
We still...
We need a key witness.

213
00:09:21.436 --> 00:09:25.231
[distant siren wailing]

214
00:09:30.737 --> 00:09:32.614
Terry: It has to be Cram.

215
00:09:33.239 --> 00:09:34.658
No. I don't trust him.

216
00:09:34.741 --> 00:09:37.786
Yeah. he worked with Gacy.
lived together. still alive.

217
00:09:41.623 --> 00:09:45.919
[overlapping
indistinct chattering]

218
00:09:46.127 --> 00:09:48.130
Man 1: [indistinct] Come on.
come on. Come here. Yeah.

219
00:09:48.213 --> 00:09:50.048
Man 2: Here we go. guys.
-Right there. See?

220
00:09:50.131 --> 00:09:51.133
Yeah. I see it.

221
00:09:51.216 --> 00:09:54.136
[siren wailing]

222
00:09:54.219 --> 00:09:57.222
[indistinct chattering]

223
00:10:02.227 --> 00:10:05.230
[siren wailing]

224
00:10:05.313 --> 00:10:06.690
[chattering continues]

225
00:10:07.607 --> 00:10:10.819
[doors close.
vehicle engines starting]

226
00:10:13.446 --> 00:10:15.657
[vehicles departing]

227
00:10:25.834 --> 00:10:30.005
John: Don't you
find this kind of ironical?

228
00:10:31.798 --> 00:10:34.801
You knock on my door
one day out of the blue.

229
00:10:35.260 --> 00:10:39.597
and poof. our lives
are changed overnight.

230
00:10:40.265 --> 00:10:44.936
Now. here we are.
two peas in a Ford.

231
00:10:45.729 --> 00:10:47.439
[flicks lighter open]

232
00:10:47.522 --> 00:10:50.442
And it's because of you that
I don't got a house anymore.

233
00:10:50.525 --> 00:10:51.735
[closes]

234
00:10:52.402 --> 00:10:54.070
That's one way to look at it.

235
00:10:54.696 --> 00:10:57.658
No other way. That's the facts.

236
00:10:57.741 --> 00:10:59.993
You had nothing to do with it.

237
00:11:01.703 --> 00:11:03.580
You're a confusing man.

238
00:11:04.289 --> 00:11:07.209
Can't tell if you're
as crazy as they say.

239
00:11:07.292 --> 00:11:09.961
I'm not crazy.

240
00:11:12.881 --> 00:11:16.051
Bet you wish you never walked
to that pharmacy. huh?

241
00:11:17.469 --> 00:11:19.680
Wished you stayed uptown.

242
00:11:19.763 --> 00:11:21.431
Bughouse Square.

243
00:11:21.890 --> 00:11:24.184
Killing kids nobody cared about.

244
00:11:26.936 --> 00:11:29.230
You know.
I think about guys like you.

245
00:11:30.231 --> 00:11:34.110
I mean. I never met
anybody like you. but...

246
00:11:34.361 --> 00:11:36.154
People say I talk a lot.

247
00:11:36.237 --> 00:11:40.325
Guys I bust. maybe five.
twenty. life. whatever.

248
00:11:40.909 --> 00:11:42.744
I don't know. you know.

249
00:11:43.495 --> 00:11:46.164
I'm just going about my day.

250
00:11:47.791 --> 00:11:50.961
At the grocery.
filling up the tank with gas.

251
00:11:51.044 --> 00:11:52.671
I don't know.
walking down the street.

252
00:11:52.754 --> 00:11:55.882
nothing but guys like you
and your little cage

253
00:11:55.965 --> 00:11:57.884
staring out your
tiny little window.

254
00:11:57.967 --> 00:11:59.761
Wondering if you're thinkin'
about guys like me.

255
00:11:59.844 --> 00:12:02.972
goin' about my day.
wanting to be us.

256
00:12:04.182 --> 00:12:05.601
It strikes me.

257
00:12:05.684 --> 00:12:08.895
I've never heard
of a detective-driver.

258
00:12:09.979 --> 00:12:13.233
Feels kind of like
a reverse promotion.

259
00:12:13.316 --> 00:12:15.443
you drivin' me around.

260
00:12:16.194 --> 00:12:17.987
I requested it.

261
00:12:19.239 --> 00:12:20.490
Really?

262
00:12:21.825 --> 00:12:23.660
What. I. I entertain you?

263
00:12:23.743 --> 00:12:25.954
Got a question I need to ask.

264
00:12:26.621 --> 00:12:28.498
Well. fire away.

265
00:12:30.291 --> 00:12:32.085
How many did you kill?

266
00:12:33.378 --> 00:12:34.546
Huh?

267
00:12:34.629 --> 00:12:36.798
How many bodies
are still out there?

268
00:12:37.465 --> 00:12:39.175
What're you talkin' about?

269
00:12:39.801 --> 00:12:42.429
In the crawlspace.
you said there's 27.

270
00:12:42.512 --> 00:12:44.097
We found 29.

271
00:12:44.305 --> 00:12:46.850
Four in the river.
that makes thirty-three.

272
00:12:46.933 --> 00:12:49.144
But there were five
that you said you dumped.

273
00:12:50.478 --> 00:12:52.939
Just numbers ain't addin' up.

274
00:12:54.024 --> 00:12:56.151
Is it really 33 bodies?

275
00:12:58.069 --> 00:13:00.488
I didn't kill any of those boys.

276
00:13:04.576 --> 00:13:09.581
[eerie music playing]

277
00:13:10.874 --> 00:13:12.834
Wanna hear a joke?

278
00:13:14.294 --> 00:13:15.545
Do I have a choice?

279
00:13:15.628 --> 00:13:17.089
So. there's these two mice

280
00:13:17.172 --> 00:13:19.258
and they're in their
Sunday finest. right?

281
00:13:19.341 --> 00:13:21.093
They got nice pants. uh.

282
00:13:21.176 --> 00:13:22.928
short-sleeve
button shirts. ties.

283
00:13:23.011 --> 00:13:25.138
and they got these Bibles
tucked under their arms.

284
00:13:25.221 --> 00:13:26.890
And they're walkin'
around this neighborhood

285
00:13:26.973 --> 00:13:28.684
and they stop at this one house

286
00:13:28.767 --> 00:13:30.519
and they knock on the door.

287
00:13:30.602 --> 00:13:31.770
And the owner. he opens up.

288
00:13:31.853 --> 00:13:33.646
And one of these mice. he says.

289
00:13:34.105 --> 00:13:38.443
"Sir. can we talk to you
about Cheesuz?"

290
00:13:38.526 --> 00:13:41.113
[eerie music continues]

291
00:13:41.196 --> 00:13:43.907
[laughs]

292
00:13:44.532 --> 00:13:47.619
Come on. Cheesuz.
That's a good one. ain't it?

293
00:13:49.329 --> 00:13:52.415
It's always handy to have a joke
in your back pocket.

294
00:13:59.297 --> 00:14:01.383
-[machine whirring]
-[man grunts]

295
00:14:01.466 --> 00:14:03.635
[metal clanking]

296
00:14:08.765 --> 00:14:10.558
Still not done?

297
00:14:10.767 --> 00:14:12.853
It's a lot of tires.

298
00:14:12.936 --> 00:14:14.980
Stacking is very easy.

299
00:14:15.063 --> 00:14:17.983
Easy. ripe. and luscious.

300
00:14:18.066 --> 00:14:20.485
That another
Butch Cassidy quote?

301
00:14:21.319 --> 00:14:23.405
And when you're done. latrine.

302
00:14:23.488 --> 00:14:26.825
Oh. I was on toilet duty
all last week.

303
00:14:26.908 --> 00:14:30.120
Man. it's a new week.
Don't live in the past.

304
00:14:31.955 --> 00:14:34.249
Hey. uh. Mr. Patil?

305
00:14:35.792 --> 00:14:37.210
Um...

306
00:14:39.295 --> 00:14:43.008
I. I was just. uh. wondering
if I could get a raise?

307
00:14:43.675 --> 00:14:44.927
A raise?

308
00:14:45.010 --> 00:14:46.803
My grams' gonna
start charging me rent.

309
00:14:46.886 --> 00:14:48.847
It's 30 a week.

310
00:14:49.347 --> 00:14:51.641
Two bucks an hour
ain't gonna cut it.

311
00:14:55.186 --> 00:14:59.191
You know. if I put
a hiring sign in that window.

312
00:14:59.274 --> 00:15:01.360
by lunchtime.
I'll have a hundred people

313
00:15:01.443 --> 00:15:05.530
lined up looking for work.
same rate. maybe less.

314
00:15:05.613 --> 00:15:06.740
You see?

315
00:15:08.491 --> 00:15:09.576
In this economy.

316
00:15:09.659 --> 00:15:12.203
you should be happy
you even have a job.

317
00:15:19.169 --> 00:15:22.380
[vehicle drives past]

318
00:15:23.923 --> 00:15:27.135
[train click-clacking
above the bridge]

319
00:15:37.771 --> 00:15:39.230
[car horn honks]

320
00:15:47.030 --> 00:15:50.241
[dramatic music playing]

321
00:16:03.088 --> 00:16:04.965
[phone ringing in distance]

322
00:16:05.048 --> 00:16:08.218
[hinges creaking]

323
00:16:10.845 --> 00:16:13.181
Bill: Take your time.
Ms. Stapleton.

324
00:16:16.059 --> 00:16:22.273
Sam. Just seeing
Sam's bracelet. it... I just...

325
00:16:22.982 --> 00:16:24.484
Water?

326
00:16:27.612 --> 00:16:29.280
[whimpering] Thanks.

327
00:16:42.419 --> 00:16:44.170
[sighs]

328
00:16:45.463 --> 00:16:48.466
Watching those
other moms testify.

329
00:16:49.884 --> 00:16:52.220
I was sure I could handle it.

330
00:16:56.391 --> 00:16:59.186
But I can't go back in there.
I'm sorry.

331
00:16:59.269 --> 00:17:01.521
You don't need to be sorry.

332
00:17:02.313 --> 00:17:07.610
His bracelet.
it was such an ugly thing.

333
00:17:09.404 --> 00:17:10.697
Now...

334
00:17:14.534 --> 00:17:17.495
[breathes heavily]
can I get it back?

335
00:17:19.247 --> 00:17:22.208
We'll figure that out
after the trial. all right?

336
00:17:28.214 --> 00:17:30.759
Samuel didn't deserve this.

337
00:17:32.802 --> 00:17:34.471
Neither did you.

338
00:17:37.098 --> 00:17:39.601
And the jury needs to hear that.

339
00:17:40.977 --> 00:17:47.859
How this changed everything
for you. for your family.

340
00:17:54.282 --> 00:17:58.787
I can't make you do anything
that you don't wanna do.

341
00:18:00.288 --> 00:18:02.416
But I know that
you've heard the things

342
00:18:02.499 --> 00:18:05.419
that the press is saying
about the boys.

343
00:18:05.502 --> 00:18:07.337
Horrible things.

344
00:18:08.838 --> 00:18:10.840
I don't watch the news no more.

345
00:18:13.510 --> 00:18:16.721
It's part
of the defense's strategy.

346
00:18:19.474 --> 00:18:23.353
saying that the boys
had it coming

347
00:18:23.812 --> 00:18:25.814
for one reason or another.

348
00:18:26.815 --> 00:18:31.277
Looking for a bigot to hang
the jury and it's not right.

349
00:18:32.070 --> 00:18:36.324
Your boy had dreams.
a mother who loved him.

350
00:18:38.368 --> 00:18:43.206
And Bessie. you have the power
to tell that story.

351
00:18:43.540 --> 00:18:46.001
That's a lot to ask. I know.

352
00:18:46.084 --> 00:18:48.420
But I have heard things
about you.

353
00:18:51.381 --> 00:18:54.176
Getting those two cops suspended
for messing with your boy.

354
00:18:54.259 --> 00:18:55.552
Beating.

355
00:18:55.635 --> 00:18:59.055
Yes. Of course.

356
00:18:59.597 --> 00:19:01.891
Holding landlords accountable.

357
00:19:04.352 --> 00:19:07.814
Knocking down
every single door that you could

358
00:19:07.897 --> 00:19:12.902
looking for your Samuel
when he was taken from you.

359
00:19:15.905 --> 00:19:18.408
And I need that strength now.

360
00:19:19.617 --> 00:19:23.913
I hate to be the one
to ask you for it.

361
00:19:27.584 --> 00:19:31.755
But I need you to get
back up on that stand

362
00:19:31.838 --> 00:19:38.094
and show the jury the love
that you have for your Samuel.

363
00:19:38.470 --> 00:19:41.681
[somber music playing]

364
00:19:51.900 --> 00:19:53.902
[knocking]

365
00:19:58.865 --> 00:20:00.533
[sighs]

366
00:20:04.079 --> 00:20:07.249
Was hoping I could talk to you
and Harold about something.

367
00:20:07.332 --> 00:20:09.042
He isn't home.

368
00:20:12.879 --> 00:20:14.798
Offer you a drink?

369
00:20:21.137 --> 00:20:24.057
It's not ideal
what I have to say.

370
00:20:24.140 --> 00:20:25.601
What else did you find?

371
00:20:25.684 --> 00:20:28.812
What else did
Chicago PD mess up?

372
00:20:29.229 --> 00:20:32.274
Oh. they tailed Gacy
a few years back.

373
00:20:32.357 --> 00:20:35.276
missing kid. nine years old.

374
00:20:36.152 --> 00:20:38.322
They said there was nothing
they could stick him with.

375
00:20:38.405 --> 00:20:41.700
but yet. here he was.
again. on their radar.

376
00:20:43.535 --> 00:20:45.746
And you had asked me
before all this started.

377
00:20:45.829 --> 00:20:50.250
do. do the police treat
every investigation the same?

378
00:20:50.333 --> 00:20:51.835
I would've said yes.

379
00:20:52.544 --> 00:20:54.421
I'd fight anybody
who said different.

380
00:20:54.504 --> 00:20:58.675
But today. I'm realizing
that I have blind spots.

381
00:21:00.844 --> 00:21:04.597
The system. the. um...
[clears throat]

382
00:21:05.849 --> 00:21:09.019
The investigations.
nobody's talking to nobody.

383
00:21:09.936 --> 00:21:11.813
We have cases being worked

384
00:21:11.896 --> 00:21:14.190
and then others
just being overlooked.

385
00:21:14.524 --> 00:21:16.485
And so. yes.
there's a better way.

386
00:21:16.568 --> 00:21:19.363
There's a. uh.
a better way of cooperation.

387
00:21:19.446 --> 00:21:23.491
of communication.
but there's walls.

388
00:21:24.868 --> 00:21:26.494
A lot of them.

389
00:21:27.871 --> 00:21:29.330
And I'm trying.

390
00:21:29.748 --> 00:21:31.791
I'm trying to break
through them.

391
00:21:34.294 --> 00:21:35.795
But I can't.

392
00:21:38.131 --> 00:21:40.383
You're here for a reason?

393
00:21:41.301 --> 00:21:44.721
Sometimes the best way to get
what we want is to make noise.

394
00:21:45.638 --> 00:21:48.600
And you got to make a lot of it.

395
00:21:48.683 --> 00:21:51.936
But people like me
tend to be transferred

396
00:21:52.604 --> 00:21:58.610
or whatever for making noise.

397
00:21:59.611 --> 00:22:01.863
So I'm supposed to do it?

398
00:22:03.198 --> 00:22:04.657
I think so.

399
00:22:06.576 --> 00:22:08.036
There are plenty of people
making noise.

400
00:22:08.119 --> 00:22:09.288
You said it yourself.

401
00:22:09.371 --> 00:22:11.039
And nobody did anything.

402
00:22:11.122 --> 00:22:14.042
You paid attention to us.

403
00:22:20.340 --> 00:22:23.760
That was Rob. Rob made it easy.

404
00:22:28.390 --> 00:22:30.433
[sighs]

405
00:22:32.185 --> 00:22:34.604
They were just boys.

406
00:22:35.230 --> 00:22:36.856
All of them.

407
00:22:38.942 --> 00:22:41.445
Why do even the most
straight forward things

408
00:22:41.528 --> 00:22:43.530
have to be a fight?

409
00:22:46.199 --> 00:22:47.909
[sighs]

410
00:22:51.329 --> 00:22:52.956
I'm tired.

411
00:23:09.472 --> 00:23:12.684
[indistinct chattering]

412
00:23:19.691 --> 00:23:22.069
Complaining to Garippo about
not enough witnesses

413
00:23:22.152 --> 00:23:24.237
being called on your behalf?
-Whoa. hey. hey. that's private.

414
00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:25.656
How did you get that?

415
00:23:25.739 --> 00:23:27.741
You can't communicate
with the judge behind my back.

416
00:23:27.824 --> 00:23:29.368
Don't you know
how this works. John?

417
00:23:29.451 --> 00:23:30.953
Yeah. Actually. I do.
I studied law.

418
00:23:31.036 --> 00:23:33.997
No. you didn't. so just stop.
Okay?

419
00:23:34.247 --> 00:23:37.751
Look. I am bending
over backwards

420
00:23:37.834 --> 00:23:39.628
trying to help you out here.

421
00:23:39.711 --> 00:23:40.963
Don't you see that?

422
00:23:41.046 --> 00:23:43.799
What... Talk to me.
What. what do you think...

423
00:23:43.882 --> 00:23:45.300
What do you think
is going on here?

424
00:23:45.383 --> 00:23:49.221
All these victims' families
saying bad things about me.

425
00:23:49.304 --> 00:23:51.181
it's all lies.

426
00:23:51.264 --> 00:23:52.599
I don't know any-a-one of them.

427
00:23:52.682 --> 00:23:53.976
And I'm just sitting there
like a dead duck.

428
00:23:54.059 --> 00:23:55.727
I can't say nothing back
and defend myself.

429
00:23:55.810 --> 00:23:57.896
I hear you.
But that's how this works. John.

430
00:23:57.979 --> 00:24:00.399
Hold on now.
Your job is to defend me.

431
00:24:00.482 --> 00:24:01.775
You should be
bringing in friends

432
00:24:01.858 --> 00:24:02.943
because I got lots of 'em.

433
00:24:03.026 --> 00:24:05.612
Have a look in my Rolodex
contact book or.

434
00:24:05.695 --> 00:24:07.072
or heck. my PDM workers.

435
00:24:07.155 --> 00:24:08.615
They'll tell you
how great of a boss I am.

436
00:24:08.698 --> 00:24:10.158
-Your employees?
-Uh-hmm.

437
00:24:10.241 --> 00:24:11.034
What the fuck. John!

438
00:24:11.117 --> 00:24:12.202
I can't bring in your employees

439
00:24:12.285 --> 00:24:13.412
because you killed most of them.

440
00:24:13.495 --> 00:24:14.997
You buried them
underneath your house.

441
00:24:15.080 --> 00:24:18.708
Hell. even that David Cram kid's
a witness for the prosecution.

442
00:24:21.503 --> 00:24:22.921
Look.

443
00:24:24.297 --> 00:24:25.716
We will get our turn.

444
00:24:25.799 --> 00:24:28.135
Prosecution first. then defense.

445
00:24:28.218 --> 00:24:31.179
and no more letters to Garippo.
please. Okay?

446
00:24:31.513 --> 00:24:33.015
I'm serious.
And if you can't do that.

447
00:24:33.098 --> 00:24:35.267
then I'm gonna quit
right now. Okay?

448
00:24:35.350 --> 00:24:39.021
I can't be fighting two battles
at the same time. John.

449
00:24:39.104 --> 00:24:40.855
I just can't do it.

450
00:24:43.191 --> 00:24:44.359
John?

451
00:24:44.442 --> 00:24:47.195
[ominous music playing]

452
00:24:47.654 --> 00:24:49.781
You know anything
about construction?

453
00:24:50.573 --> 00:24:51.533
It's easy.

454
00:24:51.616 --> 00:24:53.368
John asked me to train you.

455
00:24:53.785 --> 00:24:55.704
He said you were in the Army
or something?

456
00:24:55.787 --> 00:24:58.790
[scoffs] For a couple months.

457
00:25:00.333 --> 00:25:01.960
How long you worked for him?

458
00:25:02.293 --> 00:25:04.295
Uh. six months. Around there.

459
00:25:05.338 --> 00:25:06.548
Cool.

460
00:25:06.631 --> 00:25:08.383
Um. things to know.

461
00:25:08.967 --> 00:25:12.804
He's a cool guy.
but cracks a whip.

462
00:25:12.887 --> 00:25:15.015
He's kind of like
a perfectionist.

463
00:25:15.432 --> 00:25:17.642
Wants things on a certain way.

464
00:25:18.309 --> 00:25:19.561
Don't piss your pants.

465
00:25:19.644 --> 00:25:21.855
It's probably not as bad
as the Army.

466
00:25:22.272 --> 00:25:23.898
Why you think I left?

467
00:25:24.149 --> 00:25:26.693
I bet we have more fun
than you grunts. too.

468
00:25:27.527 --> 00:25:28.946
John's parties are out of sight.

469
00:25:29.029 --> 00:25:31.531
Free booze. whatever you want.

470
00:25:31.614 --> 00:25:33.325
Anything goes.
-Solid.

471
00:25:33.408 --> 00:25:34.910
Yeah. Hey. he can be kooky.

472
00:25:34.993 --> 00:25:39.080
but he's better than any boss
I've ever had.

473
00:25:39.873 --> 00:25:43.168
He told me to think of him
more like a friend than a boss.

474
00:25:43.251 --> 00:25:44.419
Yeah. that's true.

475
00:25:44.502 --> 00:25:46.255
Work hard. play harder.

476
00:25:46.338 --> 00:25:47.756
That's his motto.

477
00:25:49.215 --> 00:25:50.925
Uh. we're here.

478
00:25:52.594 --> 00:25:55.347
[distant indistinct shouting]

479
00:26:05.648 --> 00:26:09.444
[workers chattering]

480
00:26:09.527 --> 00:26:12.155
[distant siren wailing]

481
00:26:12.238 --> 00:26:13.698
A hot dog stand?

482
00:26:14.616 --> 00:26:16.159
John was talking big.

483
00:26:16.242 --> 00:26:18.453
He said his company
made a million a year.

484
00:26:18.536 --> 00:26:20.747
Lots of big contracts.

485
00:26:20.830 --> 00:26:22.624
I was thinking like cranes and.

486
00:26:22.707 --> 00:26:24.793
and rigs. that kind of thing.

487
00:26:24.876 --> 00:26:27.337
Yeah. that's John being John.

488
00:26:27.420 --> 00:26:28.297
He says a lot.

489
00:26:28.380 --> 00:26:29.798
Sometimes it's real.

490
00:26:29.881 --> 00:26:32.259
Other times
just a bunch of hooey.

491
00:26:32.342 --> 00:26:33.594
But. uh. who cares. right?

492
00:26:33.677 --> 00:26:35.845
I mean. five an hour
is a sweet deal.

493
00:26:36.888 --> 00:26:39.724
Grab some paint brushes.
I'll show you the ropes.

494
00:26:41.059 --> 00:26:42.227
Hey.

495
00:26:48.650 --> 00:26:51.945
[indistinct PA announcement]

496
00:26:53.655 --> 00:26:55.156
[knocking]

497
00:26:58.910 --> 00:27:00.162
Thank you for coming.

498
00:27:00.245 --> 00:27:03.957
Yeah. of course.
When did this happen?

499
00:27:04.249 --> 00:27:06.084
Couple days ago.

500
00:27:06.501 --> 00:27:08.628
Drunk maniac
ran her off the road.

501
00:27:09.254 --> 00:27:12.757
Her ribs are broken.
vertebrae. neck.

502
00:27:13.133 --> 00:27:15.594
Um. the nurse
gave her some meds.

503
00:27:15.677 --> 00:27:17.346
so she's in and out of it.

504
00:27:17.429 --> 00:27:18.764
Maryjane: Mom?

505
00:27:18.847 --> 00:27:21.182
Yeah. Sweetie?

506
00:27:22.767 --> 00:27:25.186
Wanna talk to Mr. Kunkle alone.

507
00:27:26.187 --> 00:27:28.481
Okay. Sure.

508
00:27:29.482 --> 00:27:31.276
I'll be right outside.

509
00:27:35.780 --> 00:27:38.116
She still wants to testify
tomorrow.

510
00:27:38.992 --> 00:27:41.077
Please don't let her.

511
00:27:41.536 --> 00:27:42.912
Okay.

512
00:27:52.464 --> 00:27:54.549
Maryjane. how are you?

513
00:27:55.717 --> 00:27:56.927
Been better.

514
00:27:57.010 --> 00:28:00.472
I bet. You're a tough kid.

515
00:28:03.808 --> 00:28:06.478
You believe everything
happens for a reason?

516
00:28:08.646 --> 00:28:09.773
I don't know.

517
00:28:09.856 --> 00:28:11.233
I've been doing this too long

518
00:28:11.316 --> 00:28:13.234
to have an opinion
on that matter.

519
00:28:13.985 --> 00:28:18.865
Told Billy to get a job.
any job.

520
00:28:20.200 --> 00:28:22.994
be a good guy
I could be proud of.

521
00:28:24.871 --> 00:28:26.831
What if I didn't tell him?

522
00:28:28.792 --> 00:28:31.461
What if I just let him
keep stealing?

523
00:28:32.170 --> 00:28:34.381
Would things have
turned out better?

524
00:28:35.131 --> 00:28:37.509
Would he still be here
if I kept my mouth shut.

525
00:28:37.592 --> 00:28:39.511
if I let him be himself?

526
00:28:40.345 --> 00:28:42.180
Life would be different.

527
00:28:43.390 --> 00:28:45.183
Maryjane. look at me.

528
00:28:46.726 --> 00:28:50.897
What you told him
was the right thing.

529
00:28:51.856 --> 00:28:54.484
Okay. he ran into Gacy.

530
00:28:55.110 --> 00:28:57.070
There was nothing
you could have done.

531
00:28:57.153 --> 00:28:59.615
as difficult as that is to hear.

532
00:28:59.698 --> 00:29:03.993
This is Gacy's fault.
end of story.

533
00:29:06.913 --> 00:29:09.624
Please don't take me
off the stand.

534
00:29:10.166 --> 00:29:11.418
You are in no condition.

535
00:29:11.501 --> 00:29:13.754
You said it was important
that I testified.

536
00:29:13.837 --> 00:29:17.048
I. I was speaking
generally to the families.

537
00:29:17.382 --> 00:29:20.719
And we have plenty of excellent
testimony already.

538
00:29:20.969 --> 00:29:24.306
You just need to focus
on getting better. okay?

539
00:29:24.389 --> 00:29:27.392
There's family testifying
for each victim?

540
00:29:27.642 --> 00:29:28.769
Yes.

541
00:29:28.852 --> 00:29:30.478
What about for Billy?

542
00:29:33.023 --> 00:29:34.983
That was just you.

543
00:29:38.069 --> 00:29:39.988
They all have loved ones
telling the court

544
00:29:40.071 --> 00:29:41.948
their lives mattered.

545
00:29:42.574 --> 00:29:43.992
Billy won't get that.

546
00:29:44.075 --> 00:29:45.786
His life mattered.

547
00:29:45.869 --> 00:29:48.204
Maybe not to you but to me.

548
00:29:48.747 --> 00:29:50.457
I need to speak for him.

549
00:29:50.540 --> 00:29:52.251
I can't put you on the stand.

550
00:29:52.334 --> 00:29:54.169
The doctors have you
heavily medicated.

551
00:29:54.252 --> 00:29:55.879
The defense will
use that against you.

552
00:29:55.962 --> 00:29:58.674
say that you're drugged up.
unreliable.

553
00:29:58.757 --> 00:30:00.633
Then I won't take anything.

554
00:30:02.177 --> 00:30:04.095
What about the pain?

555
00:30:05.972 --> 00:30:08.600
It's nothing
compared to losing him.

556
00:30:14.647 --> 00:30:16.691
[objects clatter]

557
00:30:22.781 --> 00:30:24.991
[hammer banging]

558
00:30:28.370 --> 00:30:29.538
Need a hand?

559
00:30:29.621 --> 00:30:32.082
No. No.

560
00:30:32.457 --> 00:30:33.792
What's eating you?

561
00:30:34.626 --> 00:30:38.088
I got yelled at earlier.
John says I'm always late.

562
00:30:38.171 --> 00:30:39.840
You are always late.

563
00:30:39.923 --> 00:30:42.050
I live in Irvin Park.

564
00:30:42.133 --> 00:30:44.177
Cram's being a crybaby because
John yelled at him.

565
00:30:44.260 --> 00:30:46.262
-[all laugh]
-Hey. join the club. pal.

566
00:30:46.805 --> 00:30:48.890
Look. he didn't can you
so that's good.

567
00:30:48.973 --> 00:30:51.727
It's simple. just work hard.
stop being late.

568
00:30:51.810 --> 00:30:52.853
If he thinks
you're doing a good job

569
00:30:52.936 --> 00:30:54.229
then you can make
even more money.

570
00:30:54.312 --> 00:30:55.564
Yeah. how?

571
00:30:55.647 --> 00:30:56.565
Gives me jobs on the side

572
00:30:56.648 --> 00:30:58.066
through a subcontracting
business.

573
00:30:58.149 --> 00:30:59.526
I can make up to seven an hour.

574
00:30:59.609 --> 00:31:00.777
Holy shit. man.

575
00:31:00.860 --> 00:31:03.280
Uh. Godzik.
getting extra work yet?

576
00:31:03.363 --> 00:31:05.949
He asked me to dig trenches
under his house for six an hour.

577
00:31:06.032 --> 00:31:07.242
What are the trenches for?

578
00:31:07.325 --> 00:31:09.536
When it rains.
it floods under the house.

579
00:31:09.619 --> 00:31:11.663
so you gotta dig so it drains.

580
00:31:11.746 --> 00:31:12.956
[vehicle approaching]

581
00:31:13.039 --> 00:31:15.166
[horn honks]

582
00:31:15.750 --> 00:31:16.835
It's John with dinner.

583
00:31:16.918 --> 00:31:18.753
Cram. go. Give him a hand.

584
00:31:19.754 --> 00:31:21.464
You wanna impress him. right?

585
00:31:21.756 --> 00:31:22.591
Yeah.

586
00:31:22.674 --> 00:31:23.592
Extra mile. buddy.

587
00:31:23.675 --> 00:31:25.260
Apologize for being late.

588
00:31:25.468 --> 00:31:27.554
If he likes you.
he'll figure something out.

589
00:31:27.637 --> 00:31:28.680
[door opens]

590
00:31:38.231 --> 00:31:41.818
Why are you always
with that coin. playing with it?

591
00:31:41.901 --> 00:31:44.237
Like a nervous tick
or something?

592
00:31:45.447 --> 00:31:47.032
It's personal.

593
00:31:47.907 --> 00:31:49.409
Oh. come on.

594
00:31:50.452 --> 00:31:51.870
What's the harm?

595
00:31:52.662 --> 00:31:55.373
Everybody's trying
to put me in jail for life.

596
00:31:56.041 --> 00:31:58.085
When everything's
all said and done.

597
00:31:58.168 --> 00:32:00.587
we ain't never gonna
see each other again.

598
00:32:02.047 --> 00:32:03.548
Can you tell me?

599
00:32:05.550 --> 00:32:08.470
-It's my dad's.
-Huh.

600
00:32:08.553 --> 00:32:11.139
He kept old coins.
two dollar bills.

601
00:32:11.723 --> 00:32:13.767
When he died.
I found them in his closet.

602
00:32:13.850 --> 00:32:15.685
scrolled away in an old shoebox.

603
00:32:16.728 --> 00:32:18.229
He a Mexican?

604
00:32:19.981 --> 00:32:21.399
Texan.

605
00:32:22.484 --> 00:32:26.321
I used to work narcotics.
undercover.

606
00:32:27.072 --> 00:32:29.407
Things I saw. wish I hadn't.

607
00:32:31.910 --> 00:32:33.912
Thought I was gonna get
found out.

608
00:32:34.371 --> 00:32:37.248
Chopped up. melted in acid
or something.

609
00:32:39.751 --> 00:32:41.503
When I get home.

610
00:32:42.712 --> 00:32:45.590
it's kind of hard to walk
through the door every day.

611
00:32:47.008 --> 00:32:49.177
Wouldn't talk to my wife.

612
00:32:49.761 --> 00:32:53.848
My kid. just blank. Didn't care.

613
00:32:56.226 --> 00:32:59.438
And then this peso shows up
out of the blue one day.

614
00:32:59.521 --> 00:33:02.524
figured my boy had found it.
got curious.

615
00:33:03.650 --> 00:33:05.318
Thought of yelling at him.

616
00:33:06.861 --> 00:33:11.033
I just slipped it in my pocket.
do something with it later.

617
00:33:11.116 --> 00:33:12.784
Carried it around with me
every day.

618
00:33:12.867 --> 00:33:14.411
Just became a habit.

619
00:33:15.870 --> 00:33:17.872
And when I was done. I got home.

620
00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:21.752
Leave the bullshit in the car.

621
00:33:21.835 --> 00:33:23.169
That's right.

622
00:33:25.046 --> 00:33:27.382
Huh. I like that.

623
00:33:28.216 --> 00:33:30.844
Wish my old man
had a coin like you.

624
00:33:34.848 --> 00:33:38.435
What's it with fathers doing
their teaching with their hands?

625
00:33:39.102 --> 00:33:41.146
That's why we have mothers.

626
00:33:42.981 --> 00:33:45.066
So your dad hit you too?

627
00:33:45.483 --> 00:33:47.402
My father raised me right.

628
00:33:49.154 --> 00:33:50.488
Got you.

629
00:33:51.031 --> 00:33:52.449
[inhales deeply]

630
00:33:52.532 --> 00:33:55.118
Me. I was a great father
to my kids

631
00:33:55.201 --> 00:33:57.203
from wife number one and two.

632
00:33:58.788 --> 00:34:01.333
There was this lady shrink
they made me talk to.

633
00:34:01.416 --> 00:34:05.379
She tried getting in my head
and she asked

634
00:34:05.462 --> 00:34:09.174
if I was relieved when wife one
and two took the kids.

635
00:34:10.216 --> 00:34:11.885
Can you believe that?

636
00:34:13.303 --> 00:34:14.388
I'm thinking to myself.

637
00:34:14.471 --> 00:34:16.139
"What the hell
kind of question is that?

638
00:34:16.222 --> 00:34:18.433
What's she getting at?"
You know?

639
00:34:21.353 --> 00:34:26.232
But now. I say to myself...
And by the way.

640
00:34:27.442 --> 00:34:29.945
it takes a real man to know
his strengths and weaknesses.

641
00:34:30.028 --> 00:34:31.321
right? You agree?

642
00:34:31.404 --> 00:34:32.406
Sure.

643
00:34:32.489 --> 00:34:36.701
So. now I say to myself.

644
00:34:40.997 --> 00:34:44.417
I probably would have been
a lousy dad end of the day.

645
00:34:45.293 --> 00:34:47.129
And lucky for them.

646
00:34:47.212 --> 00:34:49.506
they didn't
stick around to find out.

647
00:34:50.340 --> 00:34:52.425
What about you. you a good dad?

648
00:34:53.885 --> 00:34:55.929
Figures up to my kid to answer.

649
00:34:56.721 --> 00:34:58.223
Can I talk to him?

650
00:34:58.890 --> 00:35:00.809
Abso-fucking-lutely not.

651
00:35:05.271 --> 00:35:07.024
You miss 'em?
-Who?

652
00:35:07.107 --> 00:35:08.566
The kids.

653
00:35:10.568 --> 00:35:12.362
I don't think about 'em.

654
00:35:15.365 --> 00:35:17.075
Well. it's like you said.

655
00:35:17.534 --> 00:35:19.494
a real man knows his strengths
and weaknesses.

656
00:35:19.577 --> 00:35:21.830
Goddamn right about that one.

657
00:35:24.916 --> 00:35:26.418
You know what?

658
00:35:27.377 --> 00:35:30.088
Me and you.
we ain't that different.

659
00:35:30.171 --> 00:35:32.341
-You think so?
-Yeah.

660
00:35:32.424 --> 00:35:33.508
When this is all over.

661
00:35:33.591 --> 00:35:35.510
I'mma build
my house back up in a jiff.

662
00:35:35.593 --> 00:35:37.179
my businesses and everything.

663
00:35:37.262 --> 00:35:38.472
and you and your missus.

664
00:35:38.555 --> 00:35:41.933
your whole family.
you come by for a barbecue.

665
00:35:43.810 --> 00:35:45.353
It's a date.

666
00:35:47.022 --> 00:35:48.314
Good.

667
00:35:54.070 --> 00:35:55.905
[distant horn honking]

668
00:35:57.198 --> 00:35:58.241
Liz.

669
00:35:58.491 --> 00:35:59.826
Mr. Kunkle is looking for you.

670
00:35:59.909 --> 00:36:02.078
You're up soon.
We should head inside.

671
00:36:09.377 --> 00:36:12.088
[exhales deeply]

672
00:36:24.059 --> 00:36:25.477
You all right?

673
00:36:27.604 --> 00:36:30.190
He was taken
from right under me.

674
00:36:34.486 --> 00:36:36.613
I gotta tell a room
full of strangers

675
00:36:36.696 --> 00:36:39.032
how bad of a mother I am.

676
00:36:39.449 --> 00:36:41.994
I keep replaying that night
over and over.

677
00:36:42.077 --> 00:36:43.203
What if I hadn't let him stay.

678
00:36:43.286 --> 00:36:44.454
we were already running late

679
00:36:44.537 --> 00:36:47.499
or if we helped him pay
for the car. he never...

680
00:36:50.251 --> 00:36:52.588
I'm supposed to feel things.

681
00:36:52.671 --> 00:36:54.715
to know when my kids
are in danger.

682
00:36:54.798 --> 00:36:56.508
It happened all the time
when they were little.

683
00:36:56.591 --> 00:37:00.011
when Kerry broke her arm
riding her bike. I knew.

684
00:37:02.180 --> 00:37:05.600
Rob was right there.

685
00:37:07.352 --> 00:37:11.773
I talked to him.
I didn't feel anything.

686
00:37:11.856 --> 00:37:14.943
What kind of a mom
does that make me?

687
00:37:16.069 --> 00:37:18.571
-It's my fault.
-What?

688
00:37:19.531 --> 00:37:21.074
It was your birthday
for heaven's sake.

689
00:37:21.157 --> 00:37:23.243
It should've been me
going to pick up Rob. not you.

690
00:37:23.326 --> 00:37:24.995
not on your birthday.

691
00:37:25.078 --> 00:37:27.914
[somber music playing]

692
00:37:27.997 --> 00:37:30.041
-You blame me?
-No.

693
00:37:32.335 --> 00:37:33.670
I don't.

694
00:37:35.630 --> 00:37:37.173
I don't blame.

695
00:37:39.092 --> 00:37:40.218
Why would you say that?

696
00:37:40.301 --> 00:37:41.428
You think if you were there.

697
00:37:41.511 --> 00:37:42.596
this never would've happened?

698
00:37:42.679 --> 00:37:44.556
And you put that
out of your head.

699
00:37:44.973 --> 00:37:49.144
This has nothing to do
with anything that you did or.

700
00:37:49.227 --> 00:37:50.520
or didn't do.

701
00:37:53.648 --> 00:37:58.194
You have the chance to protect
our son one last time.

702
00:38:00.363 --> 00:38:03.533
Who he is. his story.

703
00:38:07.203 --> 00:38:10.206
When you're up there.
please don't hold anything back.

704
00:38:15.545 --> 00:38:16.963
[sniffles]

705
00:38:17.589 --> 00:38:20.008
Let's not keep
Mr. Kunkle waiting.

706
00:38:22.719 --> 00:38:24.846
-[indistinct chattering]
-[distant siren wailing]

707
00:38:24.929 --> 00:38:26.306
[phone ringing]

708
00:38:26.389 --> 00:38:27.724
[radio static]

709
00:38:29.893 --> 00:38:30.978
David: Thanks.

710
00:38:31.061 --> 00:38:31.853
Thank the boss.

711
00:38:31.936 --> 00:38:33.313
You know how much your bail was?

712
00:38:33.396 --> 00:38:34.648
Four hundred dollars.

713
00:38:34.731 --> 00:38:36.191
David: Shit. Michael: Yeah.

714
00:38:36.274 --> 00:38:38.568
He's gonna take it out of your
check until you're paid up.

715
00:38:38.651 --> 00:38:40.070
Yeah. that makes sense.

716
00:38:40.153 --> 00:38:42.489
What were you doing getting
fucked up in a park anyway?

717
00:38:42.572 --> 00:38:44.783
That's what John's place is for.
His garage.

718
00:38:44.866 --> 00:38:46.785
You know. bring your friends.
come and go.

719
00:38:47.118 --> 00:38:48.370
Doesn't fucking matter.

720
00:38:48.453 --> 00:38:49.788
Didn't know.

721
00:38:50.705 --> 00:38:52.415
Oh. by the way.

722
00:38:52.749 --> 00:38:54.751
John was talking
about your situation.

723
00:38:55.210 --> 00:38:57.754
With rent at your grams' plus
the four bills that you owe him.

724
00:38:57.837 --> 00:38:59.590
take a while to pay him back.

725
00:38:59.673 --> 00:39:01.008
I'll figure it out.

726
00:39:01.091 --> 00:39:03.343
I'm gonna ask him to throw me
some extra work.

727
00:39:03.426 --> 00:39:04.928
Yeah. He just wants to help.

728
00:39:05.136 --> 00:39:08.682
Said something about letting you
live with him for cheaper rent.

729
00:39:09.766 --> 00:39:11.018
-Really?
-Yeah. I mean.

730
00:39:11.101 --> 00:39:13.895
he was feeling it out.
charge like $25 a week.

731
00:39:13.978 --> 00:39:16.023
Use the extra five that
you save to pay him back.

732
00:39:16.106 --> 00:39:18.025
-Are you serious?
-Cross my heart.

733
00:39:18.108 --> 00:39:20.944
Big house. man. You'd be like
prince of the castle.

734
00:39:21.319 --> 00:39:23.697
Unless you don't want it.

735
00:39:24.197 --> 00:39:25.449
Fuck no. I want it.

736
00:39:25.532 --> 00:39:27.492
Okay. Well. yeah.
Talk to him when we get back.

737
00:39:27.575 --> 00:39:30.787
-Yeah. Uh. right on. I will.
-Okay.

738
00:39:31.413 --> 00:39:33.040
[indistinct chattering]

739
00:39:33.123 --> 00:39:35.459
Bill: This has got to stop.
Sam: Defending my client.

740
00:39:35.542 --> 00:39:37.711
No. constantly asking
for a mistrial.

741
00:39:37.794 --> 00:39:39.379
We're not doing this here. Let's
get into my chambers first.

742
00:39:39.462 --> 00:39:42.007
-But he can't keep stalling or
-I can do whatever I want

743
00:39:42.090 --> 00:39:44.301
-using any frivolous procedure.
-under the penumbra of the law.

744
00:39:44.384 --> 00:39:46.011
You. you need to be reprimanded.

745
00:39:46.094 --> 00:39:49.306
And what part of "not here"
do you two not understand?

746
00:39:49.389 --> 00:39:52.517
All right. fine. We're here now.

747
00:39:52.600 --> 00:39:54.853
Thanks. Bill.

748
00:39:54.936 --> 00:39:56.980
Bill: This trial is gonna
drag on forever

749
00:39:57.063 --> 00:39:59.066
if Sam keeps
throwing up roadblocks.

750
00:39:59.149 --> 00:40:01.568
Sorry if my client's
constitutional rights are.

751
00:40:01.651 --> 00:40:02.694
uh. inconvenient for you.

752
00:40:02.777 --> 00:40:04.154
-Yeah.
-Shh. Nip it. you two.

753
00:40:04.237 --> 00:40:06.657
Bill: You know what?
This. this roundabout

754
00:40:06.740 --> 00:40:08.033
is getting me dizzy. Right?
-Just bring him in.

755
00:40:08.116 --> 00:40:10.201
Now. yes.
-Let's just agree to disagree.

756
00:40:16.332 --> 00:40:17.542
What is going on? What is this?

757
00:40:17.625 --> 00:40:19.711
Judge Garippo:
I'm about to tell you.

758
00:40:22.589 --> 00:40:23.632
[clears throat]

759
00:40:23.715 --> 00:40:25.008
Over a week ago. Mr. Gacy

760
00:40:25.091 --> 00:40:27.177
wrote me a letter
with complaints.

761
00:40:27.260 --> 00:40:29.221
I showed it to his attorneys
who assured me

762
00:40:29.304 --> 00:40:30.597
that there was no problem.

763
00:40:30.680 --> 00:40:34.768
Today. I received
another letter from Mr. Gacy.

764
00:40:34.851 --> 00:40:37.395
demanding a response
for the previous letter.

765
00:40:38.480 --> 00:40:39.773
What are you doing?

766
00:40:39.856 --> 00:40:41.316
We talked about this.
It was settled.

767
00:40:41.399 --> 00:40:43.485
-Clearly not settled.
-Stay out of this. please.

768
00:40:43.568 --> 00:40:45.403
Hold your horses. Sam.

769
00:40:47.280 --> 00:40:50.617
Mr. Gacy. is there anything
you wish to say?

770
00:40:50.700 --> 00:40:51.993
Uh-uh.

771
00:40:52.660 --> 00:40:55.121
Nothing with respect
to the letter?

772
00:40:57.165 --> 00:40:58.416
Between you and me.

773
00:40:58.875 --> 00:41:01.878
-That's not how the law works.
-He knows that already.

774
00:41:01.961 --> 00:41:04.131
